# Emperors of Rome — Eternal Empire Timeline

This document serves as the foundational list of Roman Emperors for the Eternal Empire timeline.  
Early emperors follow real Roman history closely before diverging into the alternate timeline.

Dates are listed in:
- AUC (Ab Urbe Condita — From the Founding of Rome)
- CE equivalent in parentheses

---

# The Founders and Early Empire

## Augustus Caesar
- Reign: 727–767 AUC (27 BCE – 14 CE)
- Status: Historical
- Notes:
  - Founder of the Roman Empire
  - Established the Principate
  - Reorganized the military and imperial bureaucracy
  - Considered the First Emperor

---

## Tiberius Caesar Augustus
- Reign: 767–790 AUC (14–37 CE)
- Status: Historical
- Notes:
  - Stepson of Augustus
  - Strengthened imperial finances
  - Oversaw the empire during the ministry of Jesus of Nazareth

---

## Gaius "Caligula" Caesar Augustus
- Reign: 790–794 AUC (37–41 CE)
- Status: Historical
- Notes:
  - Infamous for instability and extravagance
  - Assassinated by the Praetorian Guard

---

## Claudius Caesar Augustus
- Reign: 794–807 AUC (41–54 CE)
- Status: Historical
- Notes:
  - Expanded Roman bureaucracy
  - Conquered Britannia
  - Improved infrastructure throughout the Empire

---

## Nero Claudius Caesar Augustus
- Reign: 807–821 AUC (54–68 CE)
- Status: Historical
- Notes:
  - Final Julio-Claudian emperor
  - Great Fire of Rome occurs during his reign
  - In Eternal Empire timeline:
    - Christianity remains a minor sect
    - Roman state suppresses martyr narratives early

