---

# The Great Divergence

## Diocletian Caesar Augustus
- Reign: 1037–1058 AUC (284–305 CE)
- Status: Divergence Point
- Notes:
  - In real history:
    - Divided the Empire into East and West
  - In Eternal Empire timeline:
    - Rejects permanent division
    - Creates the Imperial Provincial Administrative System
    - Modernizes taxation, logistics, military command, and civil administration
    - Prevents collapse of centralized imperial authority
  - Considered the "Second Founder of Rome"

---

## Constantine the Great
- Reign: 1059–1090 AUC (306–337 CE)
- Notes:
  - Christianity tolerated but never dominates the empire
  - Hellenism remains the state faith
  - Establishes Nova Roma (Constantinople) as secondary capital

---

# The Imperial Reformation Era

## Theodosius Magnus
- Reign: 1132–1150 AUC (379–397 CE)
- Status: Alternate Timeline Divergence
- Notes:
  - Last emperor to rule before the "Imperial Reformation"
  - Strengthens centralized Senate authority
  - Creates formalized succession laws

---

## Valerius Constantinus II
- Reign: 1188–1216 AUC (435–463 CE)
- Status: Fictional
- Notes:
  - First emperor to establish trans-Mediterranean industrial workshops
  - Begins large-scale imperial engineering academies

---

## Aurelius Marcellus
- Reign: 1264–1291 AUC (511–538 CE)
- Status: Fictional
- Notes:
  - Launches the Imperial Codex Reforms
  - Standardizes Roman law throughout the empire

